features: SAFER INGREDIENTS: Super Powder is formulated with simple yet powerful ingredients, including active enzymes and plant-based surfactants for targeted stain removal and deep cleaning power.

POWERFUL CLEAN: Active cleaning ingredients from mother nature, capable of tackling your dirtiest loads of laundry. Quick dissolving in all water temperatures, removes stains and rinses clean with no residual chemicals, artificial dyes or fragrances left on clothes - when we say clean, we mean it!

EXTRA CONCENTRATED: Works well with standard, commercial, and HE washing machines. Contains simple ingredients, produces minimal suds, is septic safe, and eliminates buildup left behind in clothing fibers from prior washing powders.

CLEAN WITHOUT COMPROMISE: Extra gentle with no harsh chemicals, synthethic dyes, fragrances, or other irritants, this formula was designed for those with skin sensitivities and allergies in mind. Vegan, Certified Cruelty-Free by Leaping Bunny, and Made in the USA.
WHAT'S INCLUDED: (1) 60 Load Pack of Molly's Suds Lavender Super Powder

Are Molly's Suds products safe for sensitive skin? Yes! Many of our customers have sensitive skin or eczema and that is why they use all of our products. There are no harsh or leaching chemicals and each product is clean rinsing. Are your detergents HE-friendly? Yes! All of our detergents are safe for standard, HE, and commercial washing machines. Our powder detergents do best when you add it directly to your drum and then toss in your laundry. Are your detergents septic-safe? Are they grey water safe? All of our laundry and cleaning products are septic-safe. Our Original Laundry Powder is grey water-safe, we even had it soil tested! Are Molly's Suds products safe to use while pregnant and/or for my baby's clothing? All of our products are safe to use during pregnancy. Our laundry products are all safe for use on baby clothing. Many parents choose our unscented laundry products for newborns, however our scented options are safe to use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Clean Laundry Detergent!
reviews.reviewText: I switched to Molly's Suds powder detergent almost a year ago and I LOVE it. No harsh chemicals and No dyes. Comes with or with out scent. I prefer the ocean but lavender is nice as well. Each bag comes with a small scoop and you only need one scoop of powered per load! My clothes colors are brighter, the stains come right and I fell better knowing my family is cutting back on all of the harsh chemicals. Two bags last my family of 4 about 3 months. LOVE the Molly's Suds brand

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My clothes are brighter and softer
reviews.reviewText: I was using H2O laundry soap until they quit selling in the U.S. I started a search for chemical free soap and Mollys is the 2nd new one I’ve tried. The reviews were great and I’m done looking. Clothes are clean, seem brighter and are very soft. Powder dissolves instantly in the water. I chose Ocean Mist and it’s a light clean smell. Try it, you’ll like it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Nontoxic Everyday Detergent
reviews.reviewText: I've used liquid detergents for most of my life and have been trying to find a non-toxic, non irritating, unscented alternative for a while now. I can 100% say this does the job and leaves laundry fresh without any lingering scent or buildup. I will note that this detergent is not as effective at removing Vaseline/large grease stains but it's perfect as an everyday general laundry detergent. I will be recommending it to everyone who is still using liquid detergents!

reviews.reviewText: The super power got rid of a stain that I was sure wouldn't come out. This bag is lasting a long time. I've bought their other powder laundry soaps and its definitely worth every penny!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 13, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not for me
reviews.reviewText: Sadly I cannot use this product without some difficulty. I have tried to use it twice. It cleans well and there is no residue left behind so that’s a bonus but the powder has a super fine texture like tiny dust particles and it floats in the air with the slightest movement. I have asthma and I am extremely sensitive to a numerous scents and chemicals. Even though the powder is unscented there is still something in this product that causes my asthma to flare. I will keep the product and next time I will wear a mask when i put on the next load to wash and see if that will help. If that doesn’t help I’ll just let someone else do the laundry. :)I would recommend this to anyone who is not sensitive to fine powder/dust, as the product does work well and there was no odor.

The packaging in combination with the fine powder definitely is not awesome, but I personally am not that bothered. I don’t attempt to inhale it or anything.The fragrance is subtle and nice. I got to use on flax linen bedding since natural powders are supposed to be better for them but have also been using on clothes and I am liking the results. I have sensitive skin to fragrance and have had no issues.

My absolute favourite clothing detergent. Smells amazing, I get completes from friends when they come over and I'm just done laundry, they say it smells fresh but not perfumy. The sent in the bag smells really strong when you open it, kind of like inhaling powdered hot chocolate. But once its added to the laundry and it's been in the drier, it's a very nice mild but still noticeable lingering smell. Very nice. The enzymes clearly work, they've helped pull really old smells and oils from clothes that didnt come out from any conventional detergent. Must have in a home.
Leaves "bleach like" markings on clothing that does not come out with following washes

reviews.reviewTitle: Fades clothes with a yellow tinge...while STILL not cleaning them properly???
reviews.reviewText: At first I thought this was maybe the clothes at fault, but no matter what I put in, within 2 loads there is this weird yellow tint... doesn't matter if it's blacks, reds, even blues... like a haze. All of these were done on cold water with like colours. How can this be "stain fighting" when it takes clothes that were unstained and stains them itself. It couldn't even remove basic dust from a shirt that happened to be inside out. I'm overwhelming disappointed, and won't be re-purchasing.
